<p class="template-description">Map each item to a canonical signature and group equal signatures together.</p>
<div class="template-plane-grid">
<section class="template-card">
<h3>When To Use</h3>
<ul>
<li>Objects are equivalent after normalization.</li>
<li>Need bucket, group, or aggregate items by a derived key.</li>
</ul>
</section>
<section class="template-card">
<h3>When Not To Use</h3>
<ul>
<li>Need preserve exact order as the primary constraint.</li>
<li>Need range or neighbor queries.</li>
</ul>
</section>
<section class="template-card compact">
<h3>Signals</h3>
<ul>
<li>group by</li>
<li>signature</li>
<li>frequency</li>
<li>bucket</li>
<li>canonical key</li>
</ul>
</section>
<section class="template-card">
<h3>Invariants</h3>
<ul>
<li>Equivalent inputs map to the same key.</li>
<li>The grouped value contains all items for that key.</li>
</ul>
</section>
<section class="template-card wide">
<h3>Pseudocode</h3>
<pre>groups = map()
for item in items: key = normalize(item) groups[key].append_or_count(item)</pre>
</section>
